    "a"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. It&rsquo;s given that when Tanya works <span class=\"italic\">z</span> hours, she earns <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"13 point 5 0 z\"></span> dollars. Since her hourly rate is constant, if she works 3 times as many hours, or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"3 z\"></span> hours, she will earn 3 times as many dollars, or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"3 times, open parenthesis, 13 point 5 0 z, close parenthesis\"></span>.<p>Choice B is incorrect. This expression represents adding 3 dollars to the <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"13 point 5 0 z\"></span> dollars Tanya will earn. Choice C is incorrect. This expression can be rewritten as <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"16 point 5 0 z\"></span>, which implies that Tanya earns $16.50 per hour, not $13.50. Choice D is incorrect. This expression adds 3 to the number of hours Tanya works, rather than multiplying the hours she works by 3.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
